COLLUM (
Fig. 15A
). With three transverse rows of setiferous cones/spines, 5(6)+5(6) cones/spines in anterior row, 3(4/5)+3(4) cones/spines in intermediate row and 4(3)+4 cones/spines in posterior row (lateral cones/spines of anterior row located at base of collum paraterga; paraterga of collum elevated at ca. 20º–40º.

ANTENNAE (
Fig. 15D
). Moderately long and slender, reaching to body ring 5 or 6 (male) and 4 or 5 (female) when stretched dorsally.
